{{Infobox motorsport championship | logo = [[File:Audi_R8_LMS_Cup_Logo.jpg|250px]] | pixels = | caption = | category = [[One-Design|One-make racing]] by [[Audi]] | inaugural = 2012 | folded = | drivers = | teams = | constructors = [[Audi]] | tyres = [[Michelin]] | country/region = [[Asia]] | champion driver = {{flagicon|BEL}} [[Alessio Picariello]] | champion team = MGT by Absolute | current_season = | website = {{Official website|http://www.audir8lmscup.com/en}} }}
The '''Audi R8 LMS Cup''' is a [[One-Design|one-make]] [[sports car racing]] series by [[Audi#Motorsport|Audi]] based in [[Asia]]. Audi R8 LMS Cup cars based on the [[Audi R8#Motorsport|Audi R8 LMS(GT3)]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.audir8lmscup.com/en/content/race-car|title=The Race Car|work=[[Audi]]|publisher=[[Audi Sport|Audi]]|accessdate=3 January 2015}}</ref>
== History == '''Audi R8 LMS Cup''' started in 2012 in all around the Asia. Constructor of this one make race is [[Audi]] and tyre supplier is [[Michelin]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.audi-motorsport-asia.com/|title=Audi R8 LMS Cup|website=www.audi-motorsport-asia.com|access-date=2016-03-16}}</ref>
2016 saw the debut of the new Audi R8 LMS car. Also in 2016, [[Phoenix Racing (German racing team)|Phoenix Racing]] and [[KC Motorgroup|KCMG]], join [[Absolute Racing]] as Audi R8 LMS Cup service teams.
In 2017, [[Pirelli]] becomes new official tyre partner for Audi R8 LMS Cup
2018 will see the additional of new Audi R8 LMS GT4 to the series.
