==Events== *[[660 BC]] &ndash; Traditional date for the foundation of Japan by [[Emperor Jimmu]]. * [[AD 55]] &ndash; [[Britannicus|Tiberius Claudius Caesar Britannicus]], heir to the [[Roman emperor]]ship, dies under mysterious circumstances in [[Ancient Rome|Rome]]. This clears the way for [[Nero]] to become Emperor. * [[244]] &ndash; Emperor [[Gordian III]] is murdered by [[mutiny|mutinous]] soldiers in Zaitha ([[Mesopotamia]]). A [[mound]] is raised at [[Carchemish]] in his memory. *[[1177]] &ndash; [[John de Courcy]]'s army defeats the native Dunleavey Clan in Ulster. The English establish themselves in Ulster. *[[1534]] &ndash; [[Henry VIII of England]] is recognized as supreme head of the [[Church of England]]. *[[1626]] &ndash; Emperor [[Susenyos I]] of [[Ethiopia]] and Patriarch [[Afonso Mendes]] declare the primacy of the Roman See over the [[Ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Church|Ethiopian Church]], and [[Catholic Church|Catholicism]] to be the state religion of Ethiopia. *[[1659]] &ndash; [[Assault on Copenhagen (1659)|The assault on Copenhagen]] by Swedish forces is beaten back with heavy losses. *[[1790]] &ndash; The Religious Society of Friends, also known as [[Quakers]], petitions [[United States Congress|U.S. Congress]] for the [[Abolitionism in the United States|abolition of slavery]]. *[[1794]] &ndash; First session of [[United States Senate]] opens to the public. *[[1808]] &ndash; [[Jesse Fell]] burns [[anthracite]] on an open grate as an experiment in heating homes with coal. *[[1812]] &ndash; [[Massachusetts]] governor [[Elbridge Gerry]] is accused of "[[gerrymandering]]" for the first time. *[[1823]] &ndash; [[Carnival tragedy of 1823]]: About 110 boys are killed during a stampede at the [[Franciscan Church of St Mary of Jesus|Convent of the Minori Osservanti]] in [[Valletta]], [[Crown Colony of Malta|Malta]]. *[[1826]] &ndash; [[University College London]] is founded as [[University of London]]. *[[1840]] &ndash; [[Gaetano Donizetti]]'s opera ''[[La fille du régiment]]'' receives its first performance in Paris, France. *[[1843]] &ndash; [[Giuseppe Verdi]]'s opera ''[[I Lombardi alla prima crociata]]'' receives its first performance in [[Milan]], Italy. *[[1855]] &ndash; Kassa Hailu is crowned [[Tewodros II]], [[Emperor of Ethiopia]], by [[Abuna Salama III]] in a ceremony at the church of Derasge Maryam *[[1856]] &ndash; The Kingdom of [[Awadh]] is annexed by the British [[East India Company]] and [[Wajid Ali Shah]], the king of Awadh, is imprisoned and later exiled to [[Kolkata|Calcutta]]. *[[1858]] &ndash; [[Bernadette Soubirous]]'s first [[Lourdes apparitions|vision]] of the [[Our Lady of Lourdes|Blessed Virgin Mary]] in [[Lourdes]], France. *[[1861]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: The [[United States House of Representatives]] unanimously passes a resolution guaranteeing noninterference with [[slavery]] in any [[U.S. state|state]]. *[[1873]] &ndash; King [[Amadeo I of Spain]] abdicates. *[[1889]] &ndash; [[Meiji Constitution]] of Japan is adopted; the first [[National Diet]] convenes in 1890. *[[1903]] &ndash; [[Anton Bruckner]]'s [[Symphony No. 9 (Bruckner)|9th Symphony]] receives its first performance in [[Vienna]], Austria. *[[1906]] &ndash; [[Pope Pius X]] publishes the encyclical ''[[Vehementer Nos]]''. *[[1919]] &ndash; [[Friedrich Ebert]] ([[Social Democratic Party of Germany|SPD]]), is elected [[President of Germany]]. *[[1929]] &ndash; [[Kingdom of Italy]] and the [[Holy See|Vatican]] sign the [[Lateran Treaty]]. *[[1937]] &ndash; The [[Flint sit-down strike]] ends when [[General Motors]] recognizes the [[United Auto Workers]] trade union. *[[1938]] &ndash; [[BBC One|BBC Television]] produces the world's first ever [[Science fiction on television|science fiction television]] program, an adaptation of a section of the [[Karel Čapek]] play ''[[R.U.R.]]'', that coined the term "[[robot]]". *[[1939]] &ndash; A [[Lockheed P-38 Lightning]] flies from [[California]] to New York in seven hours two minutes. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: The [[Battle of Bukit Timah]] is fought in [[Singapore]]. *[[1943]] &ndash; World War II: [[General (United States)|General]] [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]] is selected to command the [[Allies of World War II|allied]] armies in Europe. *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: U.S. President [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]] denies all appeals for clemency for [[Julius and Ethel Rosenberg]]. * 1953 &ndash; The [[Soviet Union]] breaks off diplomatic relations with [[Israel]]. *[[1959]] &ndash; The [[Federation of Arab Emirates of the South]], which will later become [[South Yemen]], is created as a [[protectorate]] of the United Kingdom. *[[1964]] &ndash; [[Greece|Greeks]] and [[Turkey|Turks]] begin fighting in [[Limassol|Limassol, Cyprus]]. *[[1971]] &ndash; Cold War: Eighty-seven countries, including the United States, United Kingdom, and Soviet Union, sign the [[Seabed Arms Control Treaty]] outlawing [[nuclear weapon]]s on the ocean floor in [[international waters]]. *[[1973]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: First release of American [[prisoner of war|prisoners of war]] from [[Vietnam]] takes place. *[[1978]] &ndash; [[Censorship]]: China lifts a ban on works by [[Aristotle]], [[William Shakespeare]] and [[Charles Dickens]]. *[[1979]] &ndash; The [[Iranian Revolution]] establishes an Islamic theocracy under the leadership of [[Ayatollah]] [[Ruhollah Khomeini]]. *[[1981]] &ndash; Around {{convert|100000|USgal|m3}} of radioactive coolant leak into the containment building of [[Tennessee Valley Authority|TVA]] [[Sequoyah Nuclear Generating Station|Sequoyah 1]] nuclear plant in [[Tennessee]], contaminating eight workers. *[[1990]] &ndash; [[Nelson Mandela]] is released from [[Drakenstein Correctional Centre|Victor Verster Prison]] outside [[Cape Town]], South Africa after 27 years as a political prisoner. * 1990 &ndash; [[Buster Douglas]], a 42:1 underdog, [[Mike Tyson vs. Buster Douglas|knocks out]] [[Mike Tyson]] in ten rounds at Tokyo to win [[boxing]]'s world Heavyweight title. *[[1997]] &ndash; [[Space Shuttle Discovery|Space Shuttle ''Discovery'']] is launched on a [[STS-82|mission]] to service the [[Hubble Space Telescope]]. *[[1999]] &ndash; [[Pluto]] crosses Neptune's orbit, ending a nearly 20-year period (since 1979) when it was closer to the Sun than the gas giant; Pluto is not expected to interact with Neptune's orbit for another 228 years. *[[2001]] &ndash; A Dutch programmer launched the [[Anna Kournikova (computer virus)|Anna Kournikova virus]] infecting millions of [[email]]s via a trick photo of the [[tennis]] star. *[[2006]] &ndash; U.S. Vice President [[Dick Cheney]] shot [[Harry Whittington]], a 78-year-old Texas attorney, [[Dick Cheney hunting incident|while participating in a quail hunt]] on a ranch in Riviera, Texas. *[[2008]] &ndash; Rebel [[East Timor]]ese soldiers [[2008 East Timorese assassination attempts|seriously wound]] President [[José Ramos-Horta]]. Rebel leader [[Alfredo Reinado]] is killed in the attack. *[[2011]] &ndash; [[Arab Spring]]: The [[Timeline of the Egyptian Revolution of 2011|first wave]] of the [[Egyptian Revolution of 2011|Egyptian revolution]] culminates in the resignation of [[Hosni Mubarak]] and the transfer of power to the Supreme Military Council after 18 days of protests. *[[2013]] &ndash; The Vatican confirmed that [[Pope Benedict XVI]] would [[Resignation of Pope Benedict XVI|resign the papacy]] on 28 February 2013, as a result of his advanced age. *[[2014]] &ndash; A military transport [[2014 Algerian Air Force C-130 crash|plane crashes]] in a mountainous area of [[Oum El Bouaghi Province]] in eastern [[Algeria]], killing 77 people. *[[2015]] &ndash; A university student was [[Murder of Özgecan Aslan|murdered]] as she resisted an attempted rape in [[Turkey]], sparking nationwide protests and public outcry against harassment and [[violence against women]]. *[[2016]] &ndash; A man [[2016 Ad Dair shooting|shoots]] six people dead at an education center in [[Jizan Province]], Saudi Arabia. *[[2017]] &ndash; [[North Korea]] [[Pukkuksong-2|test fires a ballistic missile]] across the [[Sea of Japan]]. *[[2018]] &ndash; [[Saratov Airlines Flight 703]] crashes near [[Moscow]], [[Russia]]. All 71 people on board die.
