{{italic title}}
'''''Hotelicopter''''' is an [[April Fools' Day]] video produced as a [[viral video|viral]] marketing campaign by Hotelicopter, a now defunct hotel search site, in 2009. It showed a craft based on the [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] giant [[Mil V-12]] military helicopter, leading millions to believe the world's first [[luxury hotel]]/[[helicopter]] was a reality. The video and website explained the first commercial flight of ''Hotelicopter'' was scheduled to take off on 26 June 2009 from [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|JFK Airport]] in [[New York City]], and reach the UK later that August.

In 2010, the ''[[Christian Science Monitor]]'' named the ''Hotelicopter'' as one of its top five online April Fools' pranks. ''[[The Times]]'' also included the prank in its "10 best travel April fools", rating it as 10/10.

