'''Ibrahim ibn Musa al-Kazim''' ({{lang-ar|إبراهيم بن موسى الكاظم}}), known as '''al-Jazzar''' ({{lang-ar|الجزار}}, "the Butcher"), died 825 or after 837, was a ninth century [[Alids|Alid]] leader who led a rebellion against the [[Abbasid Caliphate]] in the [[Yemen]] in the aftermath of the [[Fourth Fitna]]. He later seized control of [[Mecca]] in ca. 817, and was subsequently recognized as legal governor of the city by the caliph [[al-Ma'mun]].

